Hello Guys,

These problems have been reproduced on a fresh 4.4 instance.

Using the method above, it is not possible to phisically create a default membership (either while using Users or Groups). Executing it on the jelly runner only produces the message that the script ran successfully.

Problems that we identified:
- the script does not add groups or users to the project roles;
- it does not return any errors if the user, group or ID of the role does not exist;
- trying to add a user which belongs only to the jira-users group to the JIRA Administrators project role does not add it (and checking in the roles in the UI does not show the user entered);
- trying to add a user which belongs only to the jira-users group to the JIRA Users project role does not add the user when browsing via UI, but using the Jelly *GetDefaultRoleActors* returns correctly the user. Restarting the instance does not change this behaviour;
- changing to DEBUG level the logging of *jelly* does not produces any errors in the logs;

So, is this jelly supposed to be working like this? Is there any hidden usage to it?

Best Regards
Thiago Prisco
Atlassian Support

