The _com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.gadgets.GadgetMacro_ (com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.gadgets:gadgets-plugin:4.0) renders an iframe pointing to _org.apache.shindig.gadgets.servlet.GadgetRenderingServlet_ (registered by the _com.atlassian.gadgets:atlassian-gadgets-opensocial-plugin:3.1.9_). The symptom is that the content does not get retrieved since _gadget.showView(true);_ in line 166 _ajs.gadget.factory.js_ (_com.atlassian.gadgets:atlassian-gadgets-publisher-plugin:3.1.9_) does not result in an invocation of the showView method being inherited from the Configured -> Standard constructor from _ajs.gadget.standard.js_ (same plugin) line 172. I do not understand why this is not happening, if I debug into that line showView references the function defined in the standard class, but if I step into it is not executed. The problem has to do with the check before, I just don't see why.

After changing (_ajs.gadget.factory.js_ line 165-167)
{code}
if (gadget.getPrefs().getBool("isConfigured")) {
    gadget.showView(true);
}
{code}
to
{code}
if (true) {
    gadget.showView(true);
}
{code}

showView evaluates. Don't get me wrong here, _gadget.getPrefs().getBool("isConfigured")_ evaluated to true before and I was on the _gadget.showView(true);_ line. 

After changing this I see a loading bar but no content is displayed. The content retrieval and insertion code from _assigned-to-me-gadget.xml_ (_com.atlassian.jira:jira-gadgets-plugin:4.4.1-studio-rc2_) is executed and the DOM is enriched with the content, but the problem is that the following style from ajs-gadgets.css line 85 (_com.atlassian.jira:jira-gadgets-plugin:4.4.1-studio-rc2_) moving the content out of the canvas (until some sort of "ready for view" state is reached I guess) is never removed.

{code}
body.loading .gadget, body.config-active.loading .gadget, body.loading #config, body.config-active.loading #config {
    left: -9999px;
    position: absolute;
    width: 100%;
}
{code}

If I remove the _left: -9999px;_ instruction I can see the content. This is not a Studio specific issue, I was able to reproduce the behaviour with a vanilla JIRA and Confluence instance of the same versions. All data indicates the problem originating in the jira-gadgets-plugin so far, also I'm unsure about why showView is not executed and if this could be a problem in the atlassian-gadgets-publisher-plugin. I've also tested the Introduction gadget which showed the same symptoms, so this might be an issue with all gadgets provided by the jira-gadgets-plugin.

