In Jira 4.3.4, on line 140 of *UserSearchInputTransformer* in *populateFromQuery()*, there is an else statement that writes a superfluous warning to the logs every time that a user views the Summary of a JQL query like "assignee in (admin)" or something similar of the form "user-field in (usernames, ...)"

{code}
            else
            {
                log.warn("Operand '" + operand + "' cannot be processed in navigator for query '" + query + "'.");
            }
{code}

+To reproduce+
# In Jira 4.3.4, do a JQL search of "assignee in (admin)"
# click *Summary*
# look at the catalina.out and you will see {noformat}2011-10-18 11:36:21,177 TP-Processor25 WARN jeff kirby 696x42631x2 ajv0xc 148.92.244.123 /secure/IssueNavigator.jspa [search.searchers.transformer.UserSearchInputTransformer] Operand 'com.atlassian.query.operand.MultiValueOperand@586036e' cannot be processed in navigator for query '{assignee in ("admin")}'.{noformat}

On our system we've simply added the following to our *log4j.properties* but I decided to would file this bug anyway so that others out there can avoid a couple hours of investigation

{code}
log4j.logger.com.atlassian.jira.issue.search.searchers.transformer.UserSearchInputTransformer=ERROR, console, filelog
log4j.additivity.com.atlassian.jira.issue.search.searchers.transformer.UserSearchInputTransformer=false
{code}

